# Engine Module Patterns

## Deterministic RNG

Never use `Math.random()`. All randomness must flow through seeded `RNG` instances from `src/sim/RNG.ts`. This ensures reproducibility and testability.

```typescript
import { createLCG, randomInt, chance } from '../sim/RNG.js';
const rng = createLCG(seed);
const roll = randomInt(rng, 1, 100);
```

## Event Bus Communication

Modules communicate only through the typed event bus. Never import and call another module's internal functions directly.

```typescript
import { EventBus } from '../events/EventBus.js';
import type { GameEventMap } from '../events/GameEvents.js';

// Subscribe to events from other modules
bus.on('INJURY_OCCURRED', (payload) => { /* react */ });

// Publish events for other modules to consume
bus.emit('HOLDOUT_INITIATED', { playerId, teamId, ... });
```

## Pure Functions

Engine logic should be pure functions where possible. Given the same inputs and RNG seed, produce the same outputs. Side effects (DB writes, UI updates) happen outside the engine.

## Types First

Import all entity types from `src/types/`. Never define ad-hoc player/team/contract shapes inline.

## Testing Requirements

- Every module must have tests
- Use deterministic seeds in tests for reproducibility
- Test edge cases: empty rosters, max cap, zero-experience players
- Golden tests: verify specific seeds produce expected outputs
